name: OpioidPainMedications
title: Opioid pain medications
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This value set contains medication codes derived from opiate and opioid classes which may be of potential therapeutic benefit in treating acute or chronic pain.),(Data Element Scope: This value set contains RXNORM codes that represent opiate and opioid medication classes.),(Inclusion Criteria: RXNORM codes derived from the following:  descendants of “Opioids” in the Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) Classification System;  "Opioid Agonist" in the Food and Drug Administration (FDASPL); “narcotics” in the National Library of Medicine Medical Subject Headings (MeSH);  and "analgesics, opioids" in MeSH.),(Exclusion Criteria: Medications which are not full or partial agonists of the mu-opioid receptor, along with non-opioid medications.)
